Bubble Sort
-----------------
1. Array of length n as input
2. Check if n is already sorted
3. If yes - END
4. If No -
   1. Loop through the array from first till last element - for i=0 till i=n-1
   2. for each index of outer loop, inner loop will check adjacent element and swap in sorted order
   3. Continue till array is sorted and no swap required
   4. END

Pseudo Code
-------------------
function bubblesort(Array x){
    int length = x.length;

        if isSorted(x) {
            return x;
        }

        for i = 0 to length - 1 {
            boolean swapped = false;

            for j = 0 to length - i - 2 {
                if x[j] > x[j + 1 {
                    swap(x[j], x[j + 1]);
                    swapped = true;
                }
            }

            if not swapped {
                break;
            }
        }

        return x;
}

function isSorted(Array x) {
    for i = 0 to x.length - 2 {
        if x[i] > x[i + 1] {
            return false;
        }
    }
    return true;
}


Advantages of Bubble sort:
1. Simple algo and can work well for smaller data
2. Extra memory space not required as it is doing inplace sorting
3. In case of sorted array, it can work faster o(n)